cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with data augmentation for object recognition and scene recognition using deep learning techniques. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a deep encoder-decoder architecture to learn the synthesis function in an end-to-end manner. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with generating artificial samples using external data and learning a mapping to synthesize data. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with attribute-guided augmentation, which could be related to natural language processing tasks. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also less likely but possible as the paper proposes a deep learning approach for data augmentation.
